MOTORISTS on Scotlandâ€™s busiest motorway faced delays today after a car burst into flames on the hard shoulder.
Fire crews raced to the scene on the M8 near Kirk of Shotts at 12.45pm. The cars three occupants managed to escape from the vehicle uninjured after it caught fire.
The eastbound lanes were closed to allow the emergency services to deal with the blaze and road restriction were put in place until around 1.30pm.
No other vehicles were involved in the incident, Police Scotland said.
